  "title": "Operational Risk Analyst (Commodity Trading)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a Commodity Trading MNC with HQ in Japan, currently seeks an Operational Risk Analyst to join their expanding team.</p><p>Reporting to the Risk Manager, the incumbent will be working in a team of 3 staffs. He / She will be focus on the operational risk and internal control management. The main duties will include planning and executing operational risk initiatives such as developing operational risk-related guidelines, process mapping, documentation, business workflow, and to ensure strong internal controls and governance are in place across the organization.</p><p>Additionally, he / she will need to develop and implement operational risk frameworks, policies and procedures, monitor key risk indicators (KRIs), and report emerging risk to senior management.</p><p>Successful applicants can look forward to working in a structured environment with good company benefits.</p><p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Min a Bachelor's degree in Finance, Economics, Statistics, or a related field</li><li>At least 5 years of working experience handling operational risk in a commodity trading firm</li><li>Prior working experience in workflow documentation, operational risk management, and process design.</li><li>Knowledge in market dynamics, financial instruments, and credit risk exposure a plus</li><li>Strong understanding on operational risk management frameworks and internal control standards</li></ul><p>Interested applicants kindly use the apply button or send in your application in MS word format to Anson.lim@onyxrecruit.com.sg. (EA: 18C9213 / R21103164)</p><p>*We regret that due to potential volume of responses, not all candidates will be contacted.</p>",
